    en: "Workers 40 and older are protected from age discrimination under the federal Age Discrimination in Employment Act (ADEA, 29 USC 621). New York's Human Rights Law (Executive Law 296) goes further — covering workers 18 and older and reaching every employer regardless of size. An employer cannot fire, refuse to hire, demote, or treat a worker less favorably because of age. Forced retirement is illegal in most jobs. Age-based comments, targeted layoffs of older workers, and severance waivers that skip the OWBPA protections all signal possible discrimination."
